transcripts.text: The first time I ever heard about Bernie Sanders was when I was a waitress.  I didn't have health insurance.  I was being paid less than a living wage.  And I didn't think that I deserved any of those things.  We should have a society that guarantees 21st century economic human rights.  What makes Senator Sanders very different is that his aspiration is our aspiration.  That's the kind of leadership that I think we need right now.
